<li>State Senate: <a href="http://www.carol.net/~cox96">Howard Cox</a> is a pro-life candidate running for South Carolina Senate.<p>
<li>State House District 115: <a href="http://pages.prodigy.com/palmetto/klauber.html">Bill Klauber</a> faces incumbent challenger Lynn Seithel.<p>
</ul>
<li><b>Tennessee</b>:
<ul><li> <a href="http://www.senate.gov/~thompson/">Sen. Fred Thompson</a> was elected three years ago with 61% of the vote to fill the seat vacated by Al Gore. He's up for reelection this November.<p>  
<li><b>6th Congressional District</b>: <a href="http://www.telalink.net/~gill96/">Steve Gill</a> is running for the seat that is presently held by Bart Gordon.<p>
</ul>
<li><b>Texas</b>: Brian Babbin is the Republican candidate for the District 2 position being vacated by the retiring Charlie Wilson. Brian is a dentist from the East Texas area. Contact: (409) 283-6895. <p>
<ul>
<li><b>18th Congressional District</b>: <a href="http://www.oip.com/larrywhiteforcongress">Larry White</a> is running against Sheila Jackson-Lee (D).<p>
<li><b>20th Congressional District</b>: <a href="http://www.tddc.net/jwalker/">James Walker</a> is the Republican challenger to Henry B. Gonzalez.<p>
<li><b>25th Congressional District</b>: <a href="http://www.oip.com/perry">Brent Perry</a> to run against Ken Bentson (D).<p>
<li><b>30th Congressional District</b>: Poltical newcomer <b>John Hendry</b> is running against Eddie Bernice Johnson. CONTACT: 214-620-9868 or <a href="mailto:hendry@flash.net">hendry@flash.net</a>. <p>
</ul>
<li><b>Utah</b>: <a href="http://www.draschil.org">Tom Draschil</a> is a conservative running for Congress in the 3rd District.<p>
<li><b>Washington</b>: ex-State Sen. <a href="http://www.whidbey.net/~schaitel/ellen.htm">Ellen Craswell
</a> is in the race for Washington State's governor. For more information, contact
 her <a href="mailto:leslie.mcmillan@accessnow.com">campaign director</a>. Also running is Seattle businesswoman and ex-King County GOP chair <a href="mailto:mgbrazier@aol.com">Nona Brazier</a>.
<p><b>6th District</b>: <a href="http://GOP.psrn.com/~swhitake">Steve Whitaker</a> is running for U.S. Congress against Norm Dicks.
</ul>
<p>
<p>
<b>Conservatives in Office and Other News and Information</b>
<ul>
<li><b>Ohio</b>: <a href="http://www.nptn.org:80/state.gov/mwise/">Mike Wise</a> is the state representative from the 15th House district.  He was voted "Outstanding Freshman" by the United Conservatives of Ohio. 
<p><a href="http://www.fessler.com">Diana Fessler</a> was elected to the Ohio State Board of Education in 1994, representing the 3rd District. She is the lone voice for conservatives on the Board. CONTACT: <a href="mailto:diana@fessler.com">diana@fessler.com</a>; 513-845-8428. 
</ul>
