<html><head><title>Daily Conference Call Announcement -- ATR</title></head><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<center><h3>ATR'S Congressional Leadership Daily Update</h3></center>
<b>MEMO</b><br>
DATE:  November 24, 1995<br>
TO:  Taxpayer Activists and Radio Talk Show Hosts<br>
FROM:  Grover G. Norquist<br>
RE:  Balanced Budget and Lower Taxes or Status Quo<p>
<hr>
<P>
The present debate in Washington will decide whether America moves to a balanced budget with lower taxes, or continues the status quo of high debt, increasing deficits and government spending.
<P>
So that every taxpayer activist can be fully informed about the daily shifting tactical issues of debt ceiling limits, continuing resolutions and the budget reconcialiation budget, ATR is hosting a daily conference call at 5 PM Eastern Standard Time.  We will be joined by Newt Gingrich, John Boehner, Dick Armey, Tom DeLay, or a key staffer for a daily briefing.
<P>
Please join us by calling <b>1-703-736-7238</b> and tell the operator that you are calling in for the Americans for Tax Reform's Congressional Leadership Daily Update.
<P><center><b>Daily Conference Call<br>
<h1><center>House Speaker Newt Gingrich</center></h1>
<b>Live at 5pm Eastern Time</b>, - Replayed at 6pm & 7pm<br>
The call will last about 15 minutes.<br></b>
</h3></center>
Share this notice and the phone number with other activists in your state.  The better informed our side is, the more effectively we can promote the fight for lower taxes and a balanced budget.
<P>
Our goal over the next two months will not change:  a balanced budget by 2002 with tax cuts, but the tactics of the White House and the advocates of the status quo necessitate our being up to date in the back and forth of the daily tactical fights.
<P>
Onward.  We're winning.
<P>
<center><h3>BE INFORMED--DON'T MISS THIS IMPORTANT CALL</h3>
<a href="mailto:atr@townhall.com">Submit questions</a> to be asked of Grover Norquist or guests.
<P>
[ <a href="/atr/1.html">ATR Home</a> ]</center>
