<html>
<head>
<title>Spotlight on Medicare</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/paper2.jpg">
<center><h2>Medicare: Bankruptcy in 2002<br>
Can Medicare be Rescued?<p></center></h2>
<hr>
According to experts, Medicare will be bankrupt in the year 2002.  The GOP has recently outlined a strategy to save the Medicare trust fund.  Will the plan be able to save Medicare?  Is Medicare reform neccessary?  Will the reform bills pass?

This week's Town Hall Spotlight will focus on the many issues surrounding the 104th Congress' attempt to save Medicare.
<p>
<a href="i-monday.html">Monday, October 9, 1995</a>
<ul>
<li>Take the Town Hall <a href="medpoll.html">Survey</a> on Medicare Reform
<li>Heritage Foundation policy analyst John Liu on Medicare reform
<li>Read Senator Domenici's Senate floor speech on Medicare
<li>Read the RNC "Talking Points" on the GOP Plan to Save Medicare 
</ul>
<a href="i-tuesday.html">Tuesday, October 10, 1995</a>
<ul>
<li>Take the Town Hall <a href="medpoll.html">Survey</a> on Medicare Reform
<li>Read quotes from prominant Democrats and the new media on medicare reform
</ul>
<a href="i-wednesday.html">Wednesday, October 11, 1995</a>
<ul>
<li>Take the Town Hall <a href="medpoll.html">Survey</a> on Medicare Reform
<li>Link to the Dept. of Health and Human Services Web site
<li>Link to Thomas for the latest pending Medicare legislation
</ul>
<a href="i-thursday.html">Thursday, October 12, 1995</a>
<ul>
<li>Take the Town Hall <a href="medpoll.html">Survey</a> on Medicare Reform
<li>Read Pete du Pont's article on Medicare
<li>Heritage Foundation publications on Medicare
</ul>
<a href="i-friday.html">Friday, October 13, 1995</a>
<ul>
<li>Take the Town Hall <a href="medpoll.html">Survey</a> on Medicare Reform
<li>"Saving the Medicare system with Medical Savings Accounts" by The National Center for Policy Analysis

